{"entryId":20963,"threedpxId":"3DPX-020963","category":"Anatomy","collections":["Human Reference Atlas 3D Reference Object Library","Visible Human Female"],"keywords":["human","eye","HRA","Human Reference Atlas","organ"],"submissions":[{"submissionId":29147,"entryId":20963,"version":1.01,"workflowType":null,"parentSubmission":null,"submissionStatus":"Published","submissionDate":"2025-08-05T18:14:51.615Z","publishedDate":"2025-08-05T18:14:56.181Z","doi":null,"modifiedByUser":null,"metadata":{"title":"Eye, Female, Right","license":"CC-BY","taxonomy":"Homo-sapiens","description":"<p><strong>Description:</strong></p><p><a href=\"https://purl.humanatlas.io/ref-organ/eye-female-right/v1.2\">This reference organ, Right-eye-female (</a><a href=\"https://humanatlas.io/3d-reference-library\" style=\"color: rgb(55, 129, 209);\">https://humanatlas.io/3d-reference-library</a>) was created using data from the Visible Human Dataset, provided by the National Library of Medicine (Spitzer and Whitlock 2002). In version v1.3, the long posterior ciliary artery was added, as well as a more detailed iris. The position of the optic nerve also moved, and was made twice as thick. The muscle thickness was decreased and the position of the muscles was shifted. The levator palpebrae superioris muscle was removed as it was not deemed necessary to the eye model. The inferior oblique muscle was rotated more parallel to the plane of the cornea.</p><p><strong>Bibliography:</strong></p><ul><li>Spitzer, Victor M., and David G. Whitlock. 2002. “The Visible Human Dataset: The Anatomical Platform for Human Simulation.”&nbsp;<em>The Anatomical Record</em>&nbsp;253 (2): 49–57.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://doi.org/10.1002/(SICI)1097-0185(199804)253:2\" style=\"color: rgb(55, 129, 209);\">https://doi.org/10.1002/(SICI)1097-0185(199804)253:2</a>&lt;49::AID-AR8&gt;3.0.CO;2-9.</li></ul><p><br></p>","meshRepairModel":false,"attributionInstructions":"<p>Kristen Browne; Heidi Schlehlein. 2023. <em>3D Reference Organ fo